<br>
The rest of this post would not work in everquest the way it is now. But rather the way it should have been really.<br>
<br>
Unless otherwise noted NO weapon should have stats, if they do very minor. Verant fuqed up big time here, every weapon shodul not have a million stats on them.<br>
<br>
Highest damage potential weapons should have been specific bane weapons. By specific i mean things used on only 1 npc ectra, these shoudl be rare encounters. The best ones being boss npc droped and/or player crafted. There shoudl definately be a few of seru/emperor type weapons in the game, but it should NOT be overused, and they shoudl all have substancial lore surrounding them.<br>
<br>
Second highest damage potential weapons should have been boss npc drops. Atleast 15% worse then any comparable specific bane weapon. These weapons can also have general banes such as undead, or elemenatl ectra; the ones with general banes would be better then the ones without considering the bane, but worse when not considering it.<br>
<br>
Along with the teir 2 weapons should be the epics. They should be progressive quests that advance with you; and basically give you the ability to get a weapon slightly better then the best drop you can get from yoru current 'tier' of ability; but not as good as a drop from the next 'tier' of ability. They should be on par damage wise as the 2nd class weapons, but also have a small bane that puts them over the top of a comparable weapon. And most importantly they should have massive stats. They shoudl also have the best procs/effects. <br>
<br>
These should be LONG difficult quests. Much longer then the epics they have in the game now, much much longer. By long i dont mean kill the same named npc 1000 times hoping somethign drops, i mean tons of steps that will take real life days-weeks to complete, per teir. Not because of long camps but rather in number of steps. 'Soul marks' shoudl also be used on said quests, such that you must do EVERY step yourself. They would truely be an epic undertaking; in the sense of a long involved journey. Perhapps require a large bulk of each step to be solo work, a decent sized chunk of it taking 1 group, and mabye 1 fight per upper tier that takes a max of 2 groups. Another interesting thing to throw in would be solo 'tests'; sorta like duels where no one can assist you by spells/melee in any way while the test is going; these need not be all fights, but some definately. Also could require a soulmark from a certain number of npcs kilings within a teir to start the quest. Mabye 1 to start it and all of them to finish it. The mega fights for each epic woudl then be credited by doing standard raids; and would be credited to everyoen who contributes without having to rely on a specific drop, or your turn to loot something.<br>
<br>
Ofcourse it would be easier to just try and advance to the next teir of npc; kill somethign harder and get better weapons. But for those who are stuck in a teir, or like to quest there would be the opportunity to set themselves apart from the others within that teir by doing the ongoing epic quest.<br>
<br>
Third tier weapons would be mini boss droped/other quests.<br>
<br>
After that mundane dropped weapons/store bought weapons.<br>
<br>
<br>
That would allow a truly quest oriented game; but at the saime time allow the ability for a gruop of players to completely ignore the quest and still tear through the tiers. You could just slaughter everything, or you could slaughter everythign and undertake the quest which would allow you to do a bit more.<br>
<br>
The people who did the quest would be able to defeat the teirs with less people, because they would have better gear, but they would have to put in mega time to do it, and would thus advance through the teirs at a slower rate. You could take 50 people and blow through the teirs, progressing in gear on the way; or you coudl take 25 people dedicated to the quest, coudl tear through the same content, upgrade their gear in the same way, and then massive ammounts of time to upgrade it a bit fruther so they could do the next teir with less people then the ones who didnt put in the time.<br>
<br>
